From af4a662144884a7dbb19acbef70878b3b955f928 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Johannes Weiner <hannes@cmpxchg.org>
Date: Wed, 23 Mar 2011 16:42:24 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] memcg: remove NULL check from lookup_page_cgroup() result
Patch-mainline: af4a662144884a7dbb19acbef70878b3b955f928
References: bnc#704592

The page_cgroup array is set up before even fork is initialized.  I
seriously doubt that this code executes before the array is alloc'd.

Signed-off-by: Johannes Weiner <hannes@cmpxchg.org>
Acked-by: KAMEZAWA Hiroyuki <kamezawa.hiroyu@jp.fujitsu.com>
Cc: Daisuke Nishimura <nishimura@mxp.nes.nec.co.jp>
Cc: Balbir Singh <balbir@linux.vnet.ibm.com>
Cc: Minchan Kim <minchan.kim@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Andrew Morton <akpm@linux-foundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Linus Torvalds <torvalds@linux-foundation.org>
Acked-by: Michal Hocko <mhocko@suse.cz>

---
 mm/memcontrol.c |    5 +----
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

Index: linux-2.6.32-memcg-backports/mm/memcontrol.c
===================================================================
--- linux-2.6.32-memcg-backports.orig/mm/memcontrol.c
+++ linux-2.6.32-memcg-backports/mm/memcontrol.c
@@ -1979,10 +1979,7 @@ static int mem_cgroup_charge_common(stru
 	}
 
 	pc = lookup_page_cgroup(page);
-	/* can happen at boot */
-	if (unlikely(!pc))
-		return 0;
-	prefetchw(pc);
+	BUG_ON(!pc); /* XXX: remove this and move pc lookup into commit */
 
 	mem = memcg;
 	ret = __mem_cgroup_try_charge(mm, gfp_mask, nr_pages, &mem, oom, page);
